              "type": "text",
              "text": {
                "content": "Rain-slicked asphalt and the lingering smell of charcoal from a Taipei barbecue stand—that was the sensory baseline for the night I encountered the Drunk’s Paradox. I was in the back of an autonomous taxi, a clean, sterile capsule with an AI that insisted on its own \"safety\" while performing one of the most absurd acts of ",
